GOOS Im a huge bear on this and want this company to fail but lets get one thing straight why would they do a buyback That would be a terrible allocation of capital They effectively have more than 100 cash ROIC on new stores in certain markets There are very few brands that get this kind of return on new retail sq footage Why would you pass that up for the roughly 2 cash ROIC inversed multiple on the equity Even as a bear one needs to recognize strong internal organic ROIC vs the buyback ROIC That is either the very definition of poor capital allocation or an admission that growth sq footage is saturated which is not the case yetBuybacks on growth stocks are a sign that returns via internal organic growth is dead or the management team has no clue how to allocate capital and if the argument is to defend the multiple that is fruitless for a company traded this activelyShow More
